Reclusa=Kestral::

She let her optics fade as she felt herself seperate from her form.
She felt herself floating. Then, suddenly, everything was moving at
light speed. She was swooshing down long tunnels, lights flashing past
and colors of all sorts.  She wondered if this  was what the edge of
time looked like. Then, she stopped. She was floating in midspace
inside a giant computer.  It was like a hollow ball, only, with a
matrix core in the center of it all.  She floated around it. She heard
a voice, barely a whisper call her name and her new name. It came from
the matrix core.  She glided towards it. Just as she was about to take
a closer look, lightening flared out and grasped her. She would have
screamed, but she was seperated from her body and coudln't make a
sound.  The lightening started to pull her into the matrix core. She
struggled and kicked and fought, but it pulled her inside.  Then
blackness, nothing. No pain, no air, no fear, no happiness, nothing.
Simple and complete nothing.  Then, she saw a light. It was faint, but
it was the brightest thing she had ever seen in such blackness.  Then
a voice reached her audio receptors. It sounded like Perceptor.  She
felt herself floating towards the sound of Perceptor's voice.
